- title("Help Us Open Government")

%p We're a tiny non-profit project, free & open-source. We have a good start, but we need more resources to roll out OpenGovernment to all 50 U.S. states and beyond.

%p Want to bring OpenGovernment to your state and city, and make this free resource even better? <strong>Fund our public-mission work!</strong>

%p Become a Booster of the Participatory Politics Foundation, our registered 501(c)3 non-profit organization. PPF Boosters donate one dollar per day, that's $31 per month, to support OpenGovernment. <a href="https://crm.ppolitics.org/sites/all/modules/civicrm/bin/OneClick.php?oc_action=donate&pp=paypal&amount=31&recur=2&groups=PPF+News:PPF+Booster&receipt=45" target="_blank">Sign up on PayPal</a> -- smooth and hassle-free. 

%p <strong>Foundations</strong>: the Participatory Politics Foundation is a registered 501(c)3 non-profit organization. We seek funding partners to roll out OpenGovernmentÂ to all 50 U.S. states, cities, localities, and other countries. Download & circulate our <a href="#{ image_path 'OpenGovernment_prospectus_March_2011.pdf' }">non-profit funding prospectus</a> (in .pdf) for more information. <a href="/pages/contact">Get in touch</a> to start a conversation about how OpenGovernment can support your current program areas.

%p <strong>Political bloggers & issue-based organizations</strong>: we rely on small contributions just to keep this beta version of OpenGovernment up and running. If you value ever-greater transparency in our government and like what you see so far, please support our work by making a one-time tax-exempt contribution: <a href="http://www.opencongress.org/donate" target="_blank">donate on OpenCongress</a>.

